President Donald Trump spoke at the National Association of Manufacturers (NAM) in Washington, D.C., discussing the Administration's tax reform initiative. The speech highlighted the benefits of the Unified Tax Relief Framework, including a reduction in the corporate tax rate and ending the "offshoring model" that encourages businesses to keep foreign profits out of the U.S. The administration is also focused on reducing regulations that hinder business growth and job creation. President Trump praised the American work ethic and emphasized the goal of keeping jobs in America and creating prosperity for the country.